HEADWORD: hyperactivity
<hw>hyperactivity</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An unusually high level of
activity; -- used especially with respect to children who move around
frequently and do not sit still very long, most noticeably in school. It
is sometimes associated with <er>attention deficit
disorder</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyperaemia</ent>⟦br⟧
